title: Software Project for Computer Architecture
description: This course provides hands-on experience in using the features of modern CPUs to increase the performance and efficiency of programs. Prerequisites: CSE 30 and CSE 100 or CSE 100R; CSE 142 should be taken concurrently. Restricted to students within the CS25, CS26, CS27, CS28, and EC26 majors. All other students will be allowed as space permits.
